<p>back in Australia &amp; between 200 &amp; 300 were lying in their graves at Anzac" the majority of them were splendid fellows too.<br/>The next day the whole of the Batt were medically examined by 3 doctors &amp; those who were not up to it were sent to hospital &amp; some were sent home to Australia.<br/>Shortly after this we had a most terrific windstorm the heaviest I have ever felt, it blew nearly every tent upside down &amp; it took about 200 men to hold the big Y.M.C.A. marquee up the ropes would lift you right off your feet at times, there was no mistake about it now, Winter</p>
